Page 3
S.B. NO.
1 Day every January 23; and Kalaupapa Month every January. The
2 legislature believes that similar recognition should be accorded
3 to Brother Joseph Dutton.
4 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to honor the hard
5 work and dedication of Brother Joseph Dutton in helping
6 residents of Kalaupapa by establishing April 27 of each year as
7 Brother Joseph Dutton Day.
8 SECTION 2. Chapter 8, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is amended
9 by adding a new section to be appropriately designated and to
10 read as follows:
11 "§8- Brottier Josegh putton paj^ April 27 of each year
12 shall be known and designated as "Brother Joseph Dutton Day".
13 This day is not and shall not be construed to be a state
14 holiday.”
15 SECTION 3. New statutory material is underscored.
16 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.
